## ☁️ 6. Connecter des Services Externes (AWS S3, Email, Redis…)

L'architecture hexagonale brille ici : **un service externe = un Port (interface) + un Adaptateur**. Le Core ne sait jamais ce qui l'implémente.

### Le Pattern Universel

```
Nouveau service externe → Créer 3 choses :
  1. internal/core/ports/storage.go       ← interface (le Contrat)
  2. internal/adapters/s3/s3_adapter.go   ← implémentation (l'Adaptateur)
  3. Câbler dans internal/app/registry.go ← injection de dépendance
```

---

### Exemple A : AWS S3 (stockage de fichiers)

**`internal/core/ports/storage.go`** — Le contrat, agnostique d'AWS :

```go
package ports

import (
    "context"
    "io"
)

type FileStorage interface {
    Upload(ctx context.Context, key string, r io.Reader, size int64, contentType string) (url string, err error)
    Delete(ctx context.Context, key string) error
    SignedURL(ctx context.Context, key string, ttl time.Duration) (string, error)
}
```

**`internal/adapters/s3/adapter.go`** — L'implémentation AWS :

```go
package s3

import (
    "context"
    "fmt"
    "io"
    "time"

    "github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/aws"
    "github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/config"
    "github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/s3"
)

type Adapter struct {
    client *s3.Client
    bucket string
}

func New(bucket, region string) (*Adapter, error) {
    cfg, err := config.LoadDefaultConfig(context.Background(),
        config.WithRegion(region),
    )
    if err != nil {
        return nil, fmt.Errorf("s3: load config: %w", err)
    }
    return &Adapter{client: s3.NewFromConfig(cfg), bucket: bucket}, nil
}

func (a *Adapter) Upload(ctx context.Context, key string, r io.Reader, size int64, contentType string) (string, error) {
    _, err := a.client.PutObject(ctx, &s3.PutObjectInput{
        Bucket:        aws.String(a.bucket),
        Key:           aws.String(key),
        Body:          r,
        ContentLength: aws.Int64(size),
        ContentType:   aws.String(contentType),
    })
    if err != nil {
        return "", fmt.Errorf("s3: upload %s: %w", key, err)
    }
    return fmt.Sprintf("https://%s.s3.amazonaws.com/%s", a.bucket, key), nil
}

// ... Delete, SignedURL
```

**`internal/app/config.go`** — Ajouter les variables de configuration :

```go
type Config struct {
    // ... existing fields
    S3Bucket string `env:"S3_BUCKET"`
    S3Region string `env:"S3_REGION,default=us-east-1"`
}
```

**`internal/app/registry.go`** — Câbler l'adaptateur :

```go
import s3adapter "[[.Module]]/internal/adapters/s3"

type Stores struct {
    Product ports.ProductStore
    Files   ports.FileStorage  // ← nouveau port
}

func NewRegistry(db *sql.DB, logger *slog.Logger, cfg Config) *Registry {
    // ...
    s3, err := s3adapter.New(cfg.S3Bucket, cfg.S3Region)
    if err != nil {
        logger.Error("failed to init S3 adapter", "err", err)
    }

    stores := &Stores{
        Product: st,
        Files:   s3,  // ← implémente ports.FileStorage
    }
    // ...
}
```

> **Astuce swap** : En développement, remplacez `s3adapter.New(...)` par un `LocalDiskAdapter` qui écrit dans `./uploads/`. Le service ne voit aucune différence.

